  "body": "Today, `cast::transmute` will complain if the subjects of the transmute are different sizes. However, if those objects are pointers and the pointed-to objects are different sizes, it will not complain.\n\nThis was an issue in Servo because we had two structs that were identical before a Rust upgrade, but after a Rust upgrade some smart pointer-related optimizations changed the layout of one of the structs, resulting in a silent memory corruption. The solution was to add a `NonZero` wrapper to one of the raw pointers within the structs to disable the compiler optimization (https://github.com/servo/servo/commit/f400d79dbe307eef250329a40ef18ce7c840edf8), but this feels fragile.\n",
